This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object recognition and image classification using deep convolutional neural networks. It also involves compressing the network model, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of vector quantization methods is related to neural networks and optimization, which could also place this paper in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on compressing deep networks for resource-limited hardware could also relate to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
